            "body": "`apply_text_edits()`, no matter how it's called (e.g. manually via `<C-O>:lua test_text_edit()<CR>`), generally does not move the cursor. So it seems like the anomaly is rather the first half of your repro steps, where the cursor *does* follow the text edit.\r\n\r\nTo confirm this, change `vim.cmd.startinsert({ bang = true })` to `vim.cmd[[norm! A]]`. OTOH, `vim.cmd[[norm! Azz]]` again has the \"follow\" behavior...",
